===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} ''[[nece#Middle English|nece]]'' "niece, granddaughter" from {{etyl|fro}} ''[[nece#Old French|nece]]'' "niece, granddaughter" (Modern French ''[[nièce#French|nièce]]'' "niece") from {{etyl|VL.}} *{{term||neptia}}, representing {{etyl|la}} ''[[neptis]]'' "granddaughter" from {{proto|Indo-European|nepot-|grandchild, sister's son|lang=en}}. Akin to {{etyl|goh|-}} ''[[nift#Old High German|nift]]'' "niece, granddaughter" ({{etyl|de|-}} ''[[Nichte#German|Nichte]]'' "niece"). Displaced native {{etyl|enm|-}} ''[[nifte#Middle English|nifte]]'' "niece, granddaughter" (from {{etyl|ang|-}} ''[[nift#Old English|nift]]'' "niece, granddaughter").

